incident_updates.body: Start time : 28/02/2023 06:00 UTC End time : 28/02/2023 10:00 UTC Service impact : During operations, the following action will not be available: Creation of new EC2 credentials Creation of new trust/projet/users/role assignment Openstack password reset Creation of new heat stack Creation of new mistral cron trigger Creation of the first data processing job of a public cloud project Creation of the first k8s managed cluster of a public cloud project Creation of the first AI model deployment of a public cloud project Note that all other actions, like token or openstack ressource creation will still be possible, and token issued before the migration will also work after. To ensure 0 downtime during the migration, beware to follow the DNS without cache. Service improvement: Major upgrade of the Openstack Identity service. This will allow us to enable identity federation in the future.

incident_updates.body: Start time : 15/03/2023 13:00 UTC End time : 15/03/2023 14:00 UTC Service impact : None, except if you do not support TLS 1.3. Service improvement: Following our continuous improvement policy, we will be doing an internal maintenance to enable TLS 1.3 by default on Logs Data Platform. The cipher suites supported after this maintenance will be : * TLS 1.2 Cipher Suites: The server accepted the following 3 cipher suites: TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 256 ECDH: prime256v1 (256 bits) TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 128 ECDH: prime256v1 (256 bits) * TLS 1.3 Cipher Suites: TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384 256 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits) TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256 128 ECDH: X25519 (253 bits)
